cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.LG 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the study of network communities in social and information networks. It could also belong to cs.SD (Software Development and Programming) as it discusses the development of a conceptual model for network community structure. Additionally, it could belong to cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) as it uses empirical methods to study social networks. The paper also involves the analysis of large datasets, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
